Pretty tough to go wrong when you get to choose pretty much every aspect of the burger, from the type of meat, to the toppings, even the bun.  They customize it for you when you order it.  It&#39;s like Burger King on steroids.  Their motto should be &#34;Have it your way.......only better!&#34;

Love that they bake the buns fresh daily.  Love that they have wild game meats to try if you feel adventurous.  You know who really loves this place??  My kids!  And as any parent knows, if the kids like a restaurant, you now like that restaurant.  They go nuts over the toppings bar where they get to choose what they want on their burger, and then you throw in the fancy new coke machine that spits out a Gazillion different options of drinks.  Everyone was happy!

We will definately be back!

Went here for the first time a couple weeks ago for one of the Cubs/Cardinal games. Obviously the place was packed but hey, it&#39;s a sports bar on game night..they should be packed right? Right away i noticed an attitude with our waiter. She barely came to our table, maybe once every 40 mins or so, she would only stay for seconds at a time. I was with a group of 10 people, there was no way we could all order what we wanted in a couple of seconds, but she would just walk away! Wouldn&#39;t even bother asking if anyone needed anything. She didn&#39;t get us water, or napkins, or ketchup for our fries. She had a nasty attitude the entire time, anyway we asked for the bill which she screwed up, took her 30 mins to get us the correct bill (with attitude) and then we waited, and waited, aaaaaaand waited. 45 mins later, she STILL hadn&#39;t picked up the bill. That was the last straw, I finally complained to the manager who was really nice and covered the whole thing for us. I appreciate him taking care of us like that but the service was so awful that I really don&#39;t think I&#39;d ever go back to this place. If you&#39;re a sports bar and that&#39;s how you operate on game night...maybe stop calling yourself a &#34;sports bar?&#34; 

Also side note, I ordered the &#34;boneless wings&#34; aka chicken tenders - WORST chicken tenders I&#39;ve ever had. EVER. Barely any breading, just tasted like boiled chicken with minimum sauce/seasoning. Absolutely gross..couldn&#39;t even finish them. How does a bar mess up chicken tenders? it&#39;s just breaded chicken deep fried!! 

Avoid this place, head over to Westview instead..they got their stuff together over there!

After living out in the Burbs now for over a year I&#39;ve come to realize that this establishment Does Not Stay Open to their True Hours of Operation.

Was told by an employee when I called: &#34;That it costs a lot of money to keep the kitchen open so we shut down early if we are not busy.&#34;

The closing of their kitchen Early has Happened to me several times over the past year. After hearing their reasoning I have decided to Dine elsewhere.

This is the best pizza in the burbs.  I have been a customer for about ten years, I don&#39;t order from anywhere else.  Outside of the pizza, their Italian specialties are great as well.  Joseph&#39;s will remind you of an old-school pizza parlor.  The place is meant to be carry-out.  Don&#39;t scuff at the prices because you get what you pay for.  If you want a sub-par pizza, there are chains out there for that... &#34;Price will be forgotten long after quality is remembered.&#34;  

I have never had a problem with the service there either.  It&#39;s a very casual setting and their routine is always the same.  &#34;Joseph&#39;s pizza, pick up or delivery.&#34;  Everyone is respectful and does their job quickly and efficiently.  

If you get their thin crust, tell them you want it &#39;well done.&#39;  You&#39;ll be happy you did.  Enjoy!

I love Indian food. Sadly, I will admit I may not know the difference between really good and decent Indian food cuisine. I only know what my taste buds like so I go off of that. 

With that being said, I had mixed emotions when reading Yelp&#39;s reviews on India House, so I went with an open mind, but low expectations. My bf had purchased a Groupon a while back and figured we would put it to use since my idea of cooking up some Tasty Bites lentils and rice at home didn&#39;t exactly please him. ((I know...I can&#39;t blame the guy...))

Upon walking in, we were greeted, given a nice booth by the window, some diced up naan with a delish tomato sauce, and 9-page menu ((yikes)). Since we are both vaguely familiar with Indian dishes, we decided to go with what we knew and liked and didn&#39;t branch out - much. We decided to go vegetarian for the night and skipped out on the meat dishes. 

Appetizers:
// Samosa - Stuffed triangle pastries filled with spiced potato and peas
// Padpad Rolls with Mint Chutney - Indian spring roll. Pappadum stuffed with potatoes
// Cheese Pakoras - Homemade cheese, fritters, dipped in a batter of garbanzo

Entrees: 
// Tandoori Vegetables - Vegetables, pineapple, &amp; cottage cheese seasoned with mixed spices, grilled in Tandoor
// Malai Kofta - Mix vegetable cheese dumplings cooked in a creamy hot sauce
with herbs and spices
// Saffron Rice 

Everything we had was delicious. I have no complaints. The Malai Kofta was new to us we absolutely loved it. The blend of spices, the creaminess, and the hint of heat made for perfection. The dumplings were tender and flavorful and balanced out nicely with the sauce. The complimentary naan was slightly crispy and tasted unbelievable in the spiced tomato sauce that came with it. ((I wish I knew what it was...))

Service was also great. The servers kept our water filled, and the one manager/waiter was extremely attentive. He wasn&#39;t over the top friendly - but he was helpful nonetheless. I will agree with my fellow Yelpers that the prices are rather high. I may not go back for an a la carte dinner for that reason alone. 

I loved the decor and ambiance. The chandeliers and white linen tables give the restaurant a slightly sophisticated and elegant feel. Not to mention just the sight of sparkly and bright chandeliers makes me swoon...

Final thoughts: Great food. Good service. High prices. Would I go back? Definitely...but for the lunch buffet, or with a Groupon!

My coworker ordered some food from here last week.  I had forgotten my lunch, so he said he would share his with me as he had ordered enough food for two meals.  I rode along with him to go pick it up, and we asked the woman at the register if it would be ok for us to eat the food there, as I had decided to come last minute, and she was very reluctant to let us sit at a table.  She explained that the tables were meant for servers to attend to and that it wouldn&#39;t be right since we ordered takeout.  Now, there was not a single customer in the restaurant besides us so it&#39;s not as though we would be taking up valuable space  Finally, she grudgingly said we could, but warned us not to do the same thing next time.  Ok lady, fine.

We picked up the food and started walking toward the back corner of the restaurant in an attempt to be more inconspicuous for the sake of the woman&#39;s concern.  As we started to go, she shouted, &#34;Nuh-uh-uh-uh-uh!!  This is not a McDonald&#39;s, you can&#39;t just take your food anywhere!  That area is for the servers!&#34; and she tried to usher us into some seats in a special party room near the front of the restaurant.  At this point I said, &#34;No, I think we&#39;ll just leave.&#34;

I am appalled at the rudeness of this woman.  &#34;This is not McDonald&#39;s&#34;?  She acted as though we had brought food in from another restaurant and tried to eat it there.  We bought the food from HER, why would she treat her own customers like that?  Not to mention, we probably would have ordered at least something to drink from the server, and definitely would have tipped.  I don&#39;t think we&#39;ll be going back again.
